---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Protocol"
  description="Fieldwork protocol overview: contract version 1, length-prefixed framing, pairing, attach replay, and push registration."
>
  <section class="page">
    <div class="page-copy">
      <p class="eyebrow">Protocol</p>
      <h1>Contract version 1.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Every client starts with `Hello` and rejects contract mismatches. Local IPC uses
        bincode; mobile transport uses MessagePack. Both paths keep the same length-prefixed
        frame shape.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="doc-list">
      <article class="tile">
        <h3>Framing</h3>
        <p>Each frame is a 4-byte big-endian payload length followed by a serialized protocol message.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="tile">
        <h3>Attach and replay</h3>
        <p>`AttachSession.last_seen_seq` requests warm replay from the PTY byte ring. Stale clients receive a daemon-rendered ANSI snapshot.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="tile">
        <h3>Pairing</h3>
        <p>Pair tokens are 32 random bytes, base32 encoded, single-use, and expire after 10 minutes. The desktop must approve the request.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="tile">
        <h3>Mobile capabilities</h3>
        <p>Mobile clients can list, attach, input, resize, detach, ping, and register push tokens. Create and kill operations are rejected.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
